SIMPLE: main
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: main
<hw>main</hw> <pr>(m⟦amac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>main</ets> hand, L. <ets>manus</ets>. See <er>Manual</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A hand or match at dice.</def> <rj><au>Prior.</au>
<au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A stake played for at dice.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The largest throw in a match at dice; a throw at
dice within given limits, as in the game of hazard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A match at cockfighting.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧My lord would
ride twenty miles . . . to see a <xex>main</xex> fought.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A main-hamper.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Ainsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Main</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Main
<hw>Main</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>m⟦ae⟧gen</ets> strength,
power, force; akin to OHG. <ets>magan</ets>, Icel. <ets>megin</ets>, and
to E. <ets>may</ets>, v. ⟦root⟧103. See <er>May</er>,
<pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Strength; force; might; violent
effort.</def> <mark>[Obs., except in certain phrases.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There were in this battle of most might and <qex>main</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>R. of Gl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He 'gan advance,⟦br⟧
With huge force, and with importable <qex>main</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The chief or principal part; the main or most
important thing.</def> <mark>[Obs., except in special uses.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Resolved to rest upon the title of Lancaster as the
<qex>main</qex>, and to use the other two . . . but as supporters.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The great sea, as
distinguished from an arm, bay, etc. ; the high sea; the ocean.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Struggling in the <xex>main</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Dryden.</au>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The continent, as distinguished from an island; the
mainland.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Invaded the <xex>main</xex> of Spain.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Bacon.</au> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>principal duct or pipe, as
distinguished from lesser ones; esp. <fld>(Engin.)</fld>, a principal
pipe leading to or from a reservoir; <as>as, a fire
<ex>main</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Forcing main</b></col>, <cd>the delivery pipe of a
pump.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>For the main</b></col>, <it>or</it>
<col><b>In the main</b></col></mcol>, <cd>for the most part; in the
greatest part.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>With might and main</b></col>,
<it>or</it> <col><b>With all one's might and main</b></col></mcol>,
<cd>with all one's strength; with violent effort.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>With might and main</qex> they chased the murderous fox.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Main</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Main
<hw>Main</hw> <pr>(m⟦amac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Main</er> strength, possibly influenced by OF. <ets>maine</ets>,
<ets>magne</ets>, great, L. <ets>magnus</ets>. Cf.
<er>Magnate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Very or extremely
strong.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That current with <qex>main</qex> fury ran.</q>
<rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Vast; huge.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>main</xex> abyss.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Unqualified; absolute; entire; sheer.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧It's a <xex>man</xex> untruth.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Sir
W. Scott.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Principal; chief; first in size, rank, importance,
etc.; <as>as, the <ex>main</ex> reason to go; the <ex>main</ex>
proponent</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our <qex>main</qex> interest is to be happy as we can.</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Important; necessary.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That which thou aright⟦br⟧
Believest so <qex>main</qex> to our success, I bring.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<cs><p><col><b>By main force</b></col>, <cd>by mere force or sheer
force; by violent effort; <as>as, to subdue insurrection <ex>by main
force</ex></as>.</cd>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That Maine which <qex>by main force</qex> Warwick did win.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <col><b>By main strength</b></col>, <cd>by sheer strength; <as>as,
to lift a heavy weight <ex>by main strength</ex></as>.</cd> --
<col><b>Main beam</b></col> <fld>(Steam Engine)</fld>, <cd>working
beam.</cd> -- <col><b>Main boom</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>the
boom which extends the foot of the mainsail in a fore and aft
vessel.</cd> -- <col><b>Main brace</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd>
<fld>(Mech.)</fld> <cd>The brace which resists the chief strain. Cf.
<er>Counter brace</er>.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <cd>The
brace attached to the main yard.</cd> -- <col><b>Main center</b></col>
<fld>(Steam Engine)</fld>, <cd>a shaft upon which a working beam or side
lever swings.</cd> -- <col><b>Main chance</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Chance</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Main couple</b></col>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld>, <cd>the principal truss in a roof.</cd> --
<col><b>Main deck</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>the deck next below
the spar deck; the principal deck.</cd> -- <col><b>Main keel</b></col>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>the principal or true keel of a vessel, as
distinguished from the false keel.</cd>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p></cs>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Principal; chief; leading; cardinal;
capital.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Main</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Main
<hw>Main</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Main</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Very; extremely; <as>as, <ex>main</ex>
heavy</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧I'm <xex>main</xex> dry.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Foote.</au>
<mark>[Obs. or Low]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>main course</ent>⟦br⟧
